n_website   = \n}}\n'''''Abby's Ultimate Dance Competition''''' is an American dance [[Reality television#Reality competition/game shows|reality competition]] series on [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]]. The series encompasses twelve talented boy and girl dancers who are competing for $100,000 and a scholarship to a prestigious dance academy.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lifetime Picks Up \"Abby's Ultimate Dance Competition\"|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2012/08/06/lifetime-picks-up-abbys-ultimate-dance-competition-914111/20120806lifetime01|accessdate=December 1, 2012}}</ref> The show is hosted by [[Kevin Manno]], and judged by [[Abby Lee Miller]], [[Richard \"Richy\" Jackson (choreographer)|Richy Jackson]], and [[Robin Antin]]. Season 2 premiered on September 3, 2013, with Rachelle Rak replacing [[Robin Antin]] in the judging panel.<ref>{{cite web|title=\"Abby's Ultimate Dance Competition,\" Season Two Debuts September 3 on Lifetime|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2013/08/06/abbys-ultimate-dance-competition-season-two-debuts-september-3-on-lifetime-403311/20130806lifetime01/|work=The Futon Critic|date=August 6, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n\n===Season 1 (2012)===\n{{Episode table |total_width=72 |background=#DBE9F4 |overall=6 |season=5 |title=54 |airdate=21 |viewers=14 |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 0\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 0\n |Title           = Casting Special\n |OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2012|10|09}}\n |ShortSummary    = Meet 14 amazing dancers and their moms from around the country when they arrive in Los Angeles for the chance of a lifetime, the final audition of ''Abby's Ultimate Dance Competition''. In an intense rehearsal, the dancers must learn three different routines in only two hours. The finalists also get a chance to meet their judges, including \"Lead Judge\" Dance Moms' Abby Lee Miller, who is joined at the judges table by Robin Antin, founder of the Pussycat Doll's dance troupe, and celebrity choreographer R