sdays-cable-ratings-sons-of-anarchy-tops-charts-with-90-minute-episode-772211/cable_20121113/|publisher=thefutoncritic|accessdate=January 3, 2013}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = dbe9f4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = Happily Never After\n |OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2012|11|20}}\n |ShortSummary    = It's Witches, Wolves and Wicked Stepmothers, this week when the dancers enter the land of fairy tales. But for one mother and daughter, their fantasy of being the ultimate dancer comes to an end. Meanwhile another dancer struggles with becoming the evil Stepmother. Plus an injury during rehearsal could spell disaster for another mother and daughter duo.\n |Viewers         = 1.11<ref>{{cite web|title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: FX's \"Sons of Anarchy\" Rolls to Another Victory|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/11/21/tuesdays-cable-ratings-fxs-sons-of-anarchy-rolls-to-another-victory-870411/cable_20121120/|publisher=thefutoncritic|accessdate=January 3, 2013}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = dbe9f4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n |Title           = Bend It Like Abby\n |OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2012|11|27}}\n |ShortSummary    = The final five dancers must be very flexible this week as they try to master dance styles from around the world. One dancer starts some drama that quickly goes global after she tells her mother she overheard other dancers saying she wished she had been eliminated. Another dancer struggles to connect with the history of the people that inspired her routine. And, the bottom two dancers must undergo a flexibility test to stay in the competition.\n |Viewers         = 1.05<ref>{{cite web|title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: \"Sons of Anarchy\" Holds Off Return of TNT Dramas|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/11/28/tuesdays-cable-ratings-sons-of-anarchy-holds-off-return-of-tnt-dramas-766313/cable_20121127/|publisher=thefutoncritic|accessdate=January 3, 2013}