 Show', 'Brickleberry', 'Ink Master' & More|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/09/25/tuesday-cable-ratings-sons-of-anarchy-wins-night-tosh-0-amish-mafia-the-daily-show-brickleberry-ink-master-more/204720/|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 25, 2013}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = CCCCFF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 15\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Anything Can Happen\n |OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2013|10|1}}\n |ShortSummary    = Abby decides to mix things up with the theme for the week being \"Unconventional.\" Anything can, and will happen, starting with the remaining dancers battling Abby in a martial arts challenge. The winner's mom gets to decide which dancers land in the bottom three, leading to new fights and some surprise allegiances. To complicate matters further, each dance involves a giant, and sometimes unpredictable, prop.\n |Viewers         = 1.04<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/02/tuesday-cable-ratings-sons-of-anarchy-wins-night-baseball-tosh-0-ink-master-the-bad-girls-club-more/206385/|title=Tuesday Cable Ratings: 'Sons of Anarchy' Wins Night, Baseball, 'Tosh.0', 'Ink Master', 'The Bad Girls Club' & More|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 2, 2013}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = CCCCFF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 16\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Broadway Backstabbers\n |OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2013|10|8}}\n |ShortSummary    = Judge Rachelle Rak, a veteran of \"The Great White Way,\" leads the challenge for the \"Broadway\" themed week and blows the kids and moms away with her sassy moves. The challenge winner's mom earns the animosity of the others by bragging about her child. The pressure is on for the dancer who chooses the first solo of the season.\n |Viewers         = 1.10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/09/tuesday-cable-ratings-sons-of-anarchy-leads-the-pack-mlb-baseball-tosh